BeitEnactedbytheSenateandHouseofRepresentativesinGeneralCourtconvened:
1 1 CrueltytoAnimals;Court HearingUponConfiscationof Animals. AmendRSA644:8, IV(a)(3)
2 toreadasfollows:
3 (3) Courts shall give cases in which animals have been confiscated by an arresting
4 officer priority on the court calendar. In cases in which animals have been confiscated by an
5 arresting officer or his or her agency, a status hearing shall be held by the court within 14 days of
6 theconfiscationoftheanimals.
7 (A) A purpose of the hearing shall be to determine whether the
8 confiscation of the animal or animals was legal. Upon such a showing, the court may
9 require the defendant or appellant to post a bond or other security in an amount not
10 exceeding $1,000 for each animal in custody and/or make a determination of custody that
11 is in the best interest of the animal's health, safety, and wellbeing. If the confiscated
12 animal is co-owned by the defendant, the court may transfer the custody of the animal to
13 the remaining owner or co-owners equitably if the court determines that such is in the best
14 interest of the animal's health, safety, and wellbeing. The court may also address any
15 other matters before it as raised by either party or if it is in the interests of justice. Upon
16 request from either party or by order of the court, this hearing may include the defendant's
17 arraignment. Waiver of the arraignment by the defendant shall not waive the 14 day
18 hearingsetforthinthisparagraph.
19 (B) Such bond or security shall be posted to the court within 30 days. If
20 such bond or security is not paid within 30 days after the court orders the bond or security
21 to be posted, the animals shall be forfeited to the arresting officer, the arresting officer's
22 agency, or the arresting officer's agency's designee. The court may, for good cause, extend
23 the deadline by no more than 15 days. A court shall order the return of any bond or
24 security upon a court approved agreement of the parties or a finding of not guilty. Nothing
25 in subparagraph (3) shall negate any requirement for payment resulting from provisions
26 inRSA435:16.
27 (C) If the accused fails to appear in court without giving prior notice
28 within 3 days of the hearing date, or, if less than 3 days notice, without evidence of
29 emergent circumstances, the hearing shall take place as scheduled and the court may rule
30 onanymattersbeforeit.

